Upper Function
Returns the string with all characters in uppercase. If string is null, then the result is null.
Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.
Syntax upper(string)
Arguments string Dimension field or text string to convert to uppercase.
Example You have a column Owner_First_Name that accepts freeform entry for users to enter their first name. As a result, some names are in uppercase, some in lowercase, and others in mixed case. To convert them to all uppercase characters to make the casing consistent, use the following formula upper([Owner_First_Name])
